	<p>
	<strong>
	<ol>

	<li>Select a metal from the drop-down menu.</li>

	<li> Set the intensity and the wavelength of the monochromatic light source. </li>

	<li>By varying the driving potential in the external circuit, find the stopping potential at which
	the current flow stops.</li>
	<li>Repeat step 3 by varying the intensity and wavelength.</li>
	<li>Calculate the work function of the selected metal from the value of stopping potential.</li>
	<li>Select the metal and go through steps 3-5.</li>
	</ol>
	<br><br>

